@wholemars One year, I threw a party at the top of the Cosmopolitan for 800 people. Now that was crazy, but it requires a budget. Do you have a budget? We can party like that.

These days, I don't have a corporate card or a budget like that. But, you know, we can still have some fun.  

Here's a trick: tell Grok where you are and how long you have, then ask it to make you a path through Las Vegas for maximum dopamine. If that's not good enough, tell it to give you the adult version.

@htmella Well, that's a very different thing from what you first said.

Yes, I prefer the mastery that comes from knowing one single tool. 

Yes, I still want competitors fighting for my attention and producing many different, good alternatives.

@wholemars I've been here 150 times. If you want to have some fun, give me a call, because I know where all the fun is.

For instance, there's a guy here who has the world's largest whiskey collection. Was Steve Wynn's first sommelier, he teaches a class on how to taste things that is off the chain!

But let's be honest, we're both here to see the nerds at CES. Sometime, we'll have to do Las Vegas properly.
